org.apache.sysds.runtime.compress.cost

Interface ICostEstimate

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ComputationCostEstimator, DistinctCostEstimator, MemoryCostEstimator

    public interface ICostEstimate
extends Serializable
    A cost estimator interface. Cost here is either memory based or computation based. It is used to estimate the cost of a specific compression layout.

    • Method Detail

      • getUncompressedCost

        double getUncompressedCost(int nRows,
                           int nCols,
                           int sparsity)
        Calculate the cost of execution if uncompressed. This is used as an optimization goal to at least achieve, since if the uncompressed cost of calculation is lower than in compressed space we don't want to compress.
        Parameters:
        nRows - Number of rows in compression
        nCols - Number of columns in compression
        sparsity - Sparsity of the input
        Returns:
        The uncompressed cost.

      • getCostOfColumnGroup

        double getCostOfColumnGroup(CompressedSizeInfoColGroup g)
        If the instruction does not care about the inter column group cost, such as in memory cost or in computation cost of right or left matrix multiplication we simply estimate the cost of individual column groups.
        Parameters:
        g - Column group to estimate the cost of
        Returns:
        The Cost of this column group

      • getCostOfCollectionOfGroups

        double getCostOfCollectionOfGroups(Collection<CompressedSizeInfoColGroup> gs)
        Get the computation cost of a collection of column groups information. Since a some operations execution time depends on all compare all calculating the cost needs all the current groups to consider. This method therefore provide a method of comparing cost of all compare all.
        Parameters:
        gs - All the groups considered for this cost calculation
        Returns:
        The cost of the calculation

      • shouldTryJoin

        boolean shouldTryJoin(CompressedSizeInfoColGroup g1,
                      CompressedSizeInfoColGroup g2)
        Decide if the column groups should try to join, this is to filter obviously bad joins out.
        Parameters:

        g2 - Group 2
        Returns:

      • shouldAnalyze

        boolean shouldAnalyze(CompressedSizeInfoColGroup g1,
                      CompressedSizeInfoColGroup g2)
        Decide if the column groups should be analysed, or the worst case join should be expected. This is use full if the column groups are very small and the in practice difference between joining or not is small.
        Parameters:
        g1 - Group 1
        g2 - Group 2
        Returns:
        If the joining should be analyzed.
